cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.LO

This paper is about a new compiler for the NetKAT language, which is used for programming network behavior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses formal reasoning about network behavior, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of high-level programming languages and compiler design could also fit under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper describes the use of symbolic automata and binary decision diagrams, which are techniques used in formal verification and synthesis, suggesting a possible fit under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses performance optimization, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
